				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">LDON panel sessions (druid board)
<br />
<a href="http://pub149.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm30.showMessageRange?topicID=623.topic&start=21&stop=30" target="_blank">http://pub149.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm30.showMessageRange?topicID=623.topic&start=21&stop=30</a>
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
I was at Fan Faire, and attended both LDoN sessions.
<br />

<br />
Adventure selection -- the reason for the 30 second delay is that as soon as you click 'request adventure' your dungeon is spawned. So, if you turn it down there is a bit of clean up taking place before you can try again. Being able to change group leader and re-request immediately is a bug -- they were very interested when someone announced that as a solution for someone else's complaint.....
<br />

<br />
Selecting 'which' adventure type was apparently something they just hadn't thought of, and would take some recoding of how it works. It's a maybe. They are going to be taking their reams of data on dungeon types/themes requested/succeeded/failed etc etc and may be tweaking themes and types to make them equally desireable.
<br />

<br />
Collections: they seed 1.5x items in the dungeon, where x is the number you need to collect. But WHERE they seed is decidedly random, so large clusters with and without are quite likely. (Apparently, the random number generator really is a perfect RNG, but over VERY large strings of numbers generated). Should you ever kill every mob and still not have enough /bug while still in the adventure.
<br />

<br />
Baroness Serenya Soulhealer 
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
